Project Buxton
==============

* Sign in at https://blackradley.signin.aws.amazon.com/console

* Create a blank environment

* Clone the latest copy into then move everything including hidden files
  (this is because you cannot clones into a non-empty directory)
	git clone --depth=1 -b develop  https://github.com/blackradley/buxton.git 
	shopt -s dotglob nullglob
	mv buxton/* ./
	rmdir buxton

* Get MySQL installed, set password to password and create a database
    sudo yum -y update
    sudo yum -y install mysql-server
    sudo chown -R mysql:mysql /var/lib/mysql
    sudo chkconfig mysqld on
    sudo service mysqld start
    mysqladmin -u root password password
    mysqladmin -u root -p create cloud9database


* Install Ruby
	rvm install ruby-2.2.2

* Install the gem installer
    sudo  install rake -v '10.5.0'
    chown -R ec2-user /usr/local/rvm/gems
	gem install bundler

* Install the mysql-devel which is needed for the mysql gem and install the other gems
    sudo -i
    yum install mysql-devel
	bundle install

* Either import a backup of the database.
    mysql --user=root --password=password 
    use cloud9database9;
    source ~/db/buxton-preview-2016-11-04.sql
	
* Copy config/database.example.yml to database.yml and edit the connection to this
    development:
      adapter: mysql2
      database: cloud9database
      username: root
      password: password
      host: localhost

* Or migrate the database to the latest version
	rake db:migrate

* Run the development server
    rails s -b $IP -p $PORT -e development

* Then find a user
	mysql --user=root --password=password 
	use cloud9database;
	select * from users;
